fields.title: Welcome to Forrest Records
fields.lead_paragraph: All of the greatest punk/hardcore music - all under one roof. Whether you are looking for collectable, vintage vinyls, or the newest releases from your favourite artists, you are in the right place.

fields.name: Unshifted
fields.description: The algorhythm return with their debut LP "Unshift". This new release from the Brighton Based electro-punk duo has been called "seminal" and "a return to form".

fields.name: Days Gone
fields.description: The album that truly brought Algorhythm into the spotlight. Featuring soaring synths, along with harsh vocals and downright psychotic lyricism in places - it is easy to see why this album caused such a stir.

fields.name: re:wind
fields.description: While Git and the Merge Conflicts may be new to the scene, their debit album "re:wind" has already changed the landscape of punk music itself. The Welsh three-piece combine dazzling guitar lines, heartful lyrics and a rough rhythm section to create what many people are calling the album of the year.

fields.name: Peace Sign Tee
fields.description: An oversized style tee from scene heroes "The C Sharps" - depicting their iconic logo 'the peace sign'. This t-shirt is 100% cotton and machine washable.

fields.name: Lyrics Tee
fields.description: Boo-lean's iconic opening line to their 2015 album "Heart wrenched" is now available as a tee! The band decided to dive back into their catalogue to create a product for the die hard fans, and as always, they do not disappoint. The shirt is a cotton/wool blend.

fields.name: Midnight Mare Tee
fields.description: Four Oh Four's ghoulishly bright tee-shirt, depicting their much beloved mascot "The Midnight Mare". This t-shirt is printed in-house by Forrest Records in Cardiff, Wales. Currently on sale, so get yours now while stocks last.

fields.name: Untitled
fields.description: A reprint of the classic 1992 album "Untitled" by fan favourites Rage Against The Compiler. Includes two unreleased songs: B-sides from the original album, as well as a live rendition of their super hit "Gitting in the Way".

fields.name: Tenfoot
fields.description: Event Handlers, South Wales' post-hardcore wondergroup, are back with their newest album "Tenfoot" - an album that takes the listener to soaring highs and crushing lows. It is no mystery why this band has been a staple of the scene for so long.

fields.name: First Breath
fields.description: Great things come to those who wait. After taking four years to commuit to the album, The Initial Commits have finally dropped their debut EP "Frist Breath". If you are a fan of new-wave, electronic punk - this is the album for you.

fields.name: Float
fields.description: The remastered edition of Float's seminal self-titled album, re-printed for it's 15th anniversary. This album is a limited edition collectors item, with only 100 printed, it is an essential on any collector's shelf.

fields.name: debutAlbum
fields.description: Ex-members of The Inside Outs and Four Oh Four come together for the "hottest hardcore album of the the decade". A thrill ride from start to finish - certainly a future classic.

fields.name: F3V3R
fields.description: A divise album - called a classic but many, but not all. But with only 1,500 vinyls in circulation, no one can doubt that it is a collector's dream.

fields.name: console.error
fields.description: It is rare for a band's first EP to cause such waves. Filling moshpits up and down the country, Syntax Error's screaming guitar riffs will get even the most staunch wallhugger moving.

fields.name: The Frontman
fields.description: The Inside Outs' new product line: frontmen, on shirts. Our only wish is that it was their frontman and not Alex Turner...

fields.name: The Classic Grey
fields.description: The classic, the timeless, the plain grey tee. This t-shirt is made by your very own Forrest Records! Heavy duty, quality material; who says you have to pay top dollar for top quality. All Forrest records clothing are unisex.

fields.name: The Classic White
fields.description: The classic, the timeless, the plain white tee. This t-shirt is made by your very own Forrest Records! Heavy duty, quality material; who says you have to pay top dollar for top quality. All Forrest records clothing are unisex.

fields.name: Don't Fear the Reaper (Pink)
fields.description: ASYNC bring us a colourful number, incorporating their fan-favourite mascot "Grimmy". This pink edition is a rare, limited time product. Sale of this product will cease on the 01/12/2022.

fields.name: Caching Checks
fields.description: Everyone knows Johnny Cache's signature check shirt - a legendary icon in the scene. Well, now you have the chance to make this signature staple your own!

fields.name: The Classic Black (Vest)
fields.description: The classic, the timeless, the plain black vest. This t-shirt is made by your very own Forrest Records! Heavy duty, quality material; who says you have to pay top dollar for top quality. All Forrest records clothing are unisex.

fields.name: Neo Tokyo Tee
fields.description: A Rage Against the Compiler t-shirt from their legendary, sold-out, 1995 tour: "Neo Tokyo". With only 10 of these t-shirts available - this is the ultimate collectors' item.

fields.title: Welcome to Forrest Records!
fields.content:
The home of South Wales punk and hardcore has arrived! We are a business run by bands for bands, dedicated to bringing all of your favourite artists to you at an affordable price.

 

We are a small business, starting in the dying embers of 2022, comprising of ex-members of The Initial Commits, Four Oh Four, and Syntax Error. We have seen the full potential of our scene to break out onto the world stage, and we want to help that happen.

 

If that sounds interesting to you, please consider taking a look at our products.

fields.title: Rage Against the Compiler Announce 2023 Tour
fields.content:
THEY. ARE. BACK.

 

After a ten-year hiatus, Rage Against the Compiler have announced they are returning for a UK tour in early 2023, for the 15 year of their landscape-changing album ‘Untitled’. They will be embarking on fourteen dates, alongside scene heroes The C Sharps and Float.

 

Tickets are yet to be announced, watch this space for further updates.

fields.title: Forrest Records Charity Event: Dec 2nd 2022
fields.content:
It was headline news within the scene, when four months ago, the contents of Async’s tour van were stolen in the midst of their European tour - costing the band a whopping £14,000.

 

We here at Forrest Records want to give back to a band that has given so much to the scene over the years, who have represented our scene on the national and international level. We will be hosting a charity event to raise money to help the band recuperate their losses.

 

But… there’s a twist.

 

This will not be your run-of-the-mill gig night. A Forrest Records all-star line-up will be combining together to make three supergroups - taking requests, playing all the classics, as well as some other surprises.

 

If you would like to attend, please contact us here.

fields.title: Four Oh Four and Event Handlers Joint EP in the Works.
fields.content:
What’s better than a Four Oh Four album? What’s better than an Event Handlers album? Let us tell you…

 

A Four Oh Four/Event Handlers joint album, which is coming in the spring of 2023. The two scene-heavyweights, and long time tour-pals, are joining forcing to put out what we here at Forrest records are already anticipating to be the album of the year for 2023.

 

No title, track listing, or cover art has been revealed as of yet - but there has been talk that this album will include features from other ‘established’ bands from the scene. Watch this space to keep up to date with everything.

 

 

Update: 3rd October 2022

 

Three features have been announced for the forthcoming album, and boy were they worth the wait: Scott Davies of Float, Adam Key of Git & the Merge Conflicts, and Spencer Ainsworth of Panic @ the Distro will be joining in on what is already a mammoth project. Only 6 months left to go!

fields.title: Algorhythm Sign to Tonedef Records.
fields.content:
Despite there short career, Algorhythm have already clearly established themselves as part of the South Wales hardcore scene.

 

Now, they are going to the next level.

 

As of 1st October, 2022, the Algorhythm have signed to the Tonedef dynasty for a 3-record deal. We are excited to see where they go in the future, backed by a label with as much experience and passion.
